/* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
* JINZORA
* (Jinzora Is Not Zina OR Andromeda)
*
* Jinzora is a graphical interface to your MP3 collection, a personal
* jukebox, an MP3 streamer.  It is similar to Andromeda, and was originaly 
* a port of the Zina project (http://www.pancake.org/jinzora.html) but has been
* re-written from almost the groud up to add many new features 
* and to make it easier to use.  It is released under the GNU GPL.
* 
* Jinzora Author:
* Ross Carlson: ross@jasbone.com
* http://www.jasbone.com/jinzora
* Support: http://www.jinzora.org/modules.php?op=modload&name=XForum&file=index
* Downloads: http://www.jinzora.org/modules.php?op=modload&name=jz_download&file=index
* License: GNU GPL <http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html>
* 
* Contributors:
* Please see http://www.jinzora.org/modules.php?op=modload&name=jz_whois&file=index
*
* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * */

Jinzora 1.0

* SEC: Big Security Fix! Now when on the login screen you can not see the header drop downs until logged in (sorry about that one!)
* NEW: Big Addition! Added an embedded WMP option - now media is played in a embedded player rather than streamed (see docs for details)!!!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a new Java Applet for file uploads, VERY SLICK! Many thanks to Laurent on this one!!!
* NEW: Big Addition! Playlists generation is now linked directly to playlists.php file for much better playlist generation - HUGE for Mambo
* NEW: Big Addition! Added "Slimzora" - A "slim" interface for Jinzora with stripped down functionality
* NEW: Big Addition! Added full support for the MDPro CMS
* NEW: Big Addition! Added full support for the CPGNuke CMS
* NEW: Big Addition! You can now click on Aritsts or Albums in the header to view a search page to search by alpha/letter!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a "Barge" feature to Jukebox, now you can insert media at the current location in the playlist without recreating the playlist!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a complete playlist view to Jukebox mode, including the ability to jump to any track in the list!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added some new bulk editing tools to make filename management easier!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a Lo-Fi track display and user type!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added the ability to add track thumbnails
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a new Search for New Media tool - shows all your newly added stuff!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added download counting - tracks each time an item is downloaded
* NEW: You can now use the toptracks.php file standalone by adding ?standalone=true in the URL field
* NEW: Added the ability to put a footer.txt file to be displayed in the footer - just like the header.txt file
* NEW: You can now disable all play icons everyone except for tracks (better for public sites where artist plays aren't valid)
* NEW: You can now easily exclude items from the info pages (and unhide from the menus)
* NEW: Added the display of the file date to the track info page
* NEW: Now sub item numbers are shown in the header (if turned on)
* NEW: You can now disable the random play icons and set it so you can decide who can see the info links (admins or all)
* NEW: Much better support for .rm files
* NEW: You can now set "all" as an audio_type to display "all" items in a directory unfiltered
* NEW: Now when the language is changed on the fly the docs will change to that language as well (if they exist, English if not)
* NEW: You can now completely disable playlists
* NEW: Major performance updates for XMMS based Jukebox mode - only reads the bare minium of data once to make it faster
* NEW: You can specify how many columns the album art is displayed in
* BUG: Fixed an issue when viewing items with sub folders in 1 dir mode
* BUG: When you change the theme on the fly the popup pages will change too
* BUG: Fixed an issue with the getID3 classes dying on bad ID3v2 tags - MANY thanks to Allan at getID3.org!!!
* BUG: Fixed the login issue with CMS mode where you would see "You have no access" but then get access
* BUG: Fixed playback of .rm files - single files only for now...
* BUG: Fixed some issues with playlist generation (for stored playlists)
* BUG: Fixed a bug where ID3 comments are displayed when they shouldn't be
* BUG: Fixed an issue with the display of artist/album info in top tracks/highest rated
* BUG: Fixed an issue with ID3 updating of a single album
* BUG: Fixed a bug with the display of .lyrics files
* BUG: Fixed many bugs with the menu system when there are single quotes in the path
* BUG: Fixed many bugs with 1 directory mode
* BUG: Fixed an issue with Playlist display
* CHG: Simplified the installer to help make installations easier :-)
* CHG: Now the english language file is loaded first, so if there are missing translations something will still show
* CHG: Removed the Play Album and Change Art links below the album art (I think this looked bad)
* CHG: Now you have the option of disabling automatic lyrics searching
* CHG: Change the size of the default album art from 100x100 to 200x200
* CHG: Now in Jukebox mode while at the "login" screen the hotkeys are disabled
* CHG: Moved the search function to a seperate menu in Album mode, added Echo

Jinzora 0.9.5 (2.27.04)

* SEC: Big Security Fix! Added MD5 hashing to all passwords, thanks Joe!
* NEW: HUGE ADDITION!!! We've added a new "caching" system to cache all track information for up to 500% faster display of data!!!
* NEW: Big Addition! Now when writing ID3 tags IF the album art and lyrics are found they are written to the files!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added support for the Mambo CMS! Beta so far, but it works great for me!!!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added track play counting, now Jinzora can track how many times a track has been added to a playlist
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a track "discussion" system - now users can enter personal comments about any track in Jinzora!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a star based track rating system!!! Now users can rate tracks from 0-5 stars!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a "Suggestion" system based on the user ratings!!!
* NEW: Big Addition! You can now have Jinzora point out newly (user definable) discovered content
* NEW: Big Addition! You can now display the top X most played tracks within the system
* NEW: Big Addition! There is now a Jinzora RSS Newsfeed (2 of them) for most played and highest rated tracks!
* NEW: Big Addition! I've added a new menu system (thanks Mambo) for playing and managing media on the tracks page
* NEW: Big Addition! Jinzora now has a full server side Jukebox feature! Play media directly on the server - fully supported in Linux & Windows! - please see the help for details
* NEW: Cool Addition! In Jukebox mode Jinzora will display the album art of the current playing track, if available
* NEW: You can now upload album and artist images using the web form instead of the filesystem
* NEW: You can now add .fake.lnk tracks to have Jinzora link to an outside site. Please see help for details
* NEW: You can now updated ID3 tags on a per album basis (if logged in as admin)
* NEW: You can now rate and comment on Genres/Artists/Albums as well as songs...
* NEW: Added 2 new themes - Sandstone and Bluesteel - let me know if you hate them...
* NEW: Added a Portuguese (Brazilian) translation - Thanks to Cherem!
* NEW: Added a Bulgarian translation - Thanks to Martin!
* NEW: Some minor tweaks to the themes for IE (since I only use <a href="http://www.mozilla.org/firebird">Firebird</a> now...)
* NEW: You can now turn off the display of track bitrate, frequency, filesize and lenght, all individually
* NEW: You can now disabled right mouse clicks to help protect your content (but we think this is bad)
* BUG: Fixed an issue with special characters in some playlists
* BUG: Fixed the user manager in PHP/NSNNuke modes
* CHG: I'm not NOT including all the themes with the distrubution to slim it down. I'll be including "Sandstone" and the cms-theme (the others will be in downloads)
* CHG: I'm not NOT including the Shoutcast files with the distrubution, and will post them on the downloads page
* CHG: Now when dispalying new items, it will tell you "New from last Wednesday" etc.
* CHG: The popup windows now read the current theme
* CHG: Usernames are not non-case sensitive
* CHG: Big Changes! I changed a lot of the way that CMS integration works to support more CMSes - could be buggy, please let me know
* CHG: Removed the old class I was using to read/write ID3 tags, now using getID3 only
* CHG: Now when you change themes on the fly Jinzora will keep you on the page you were on, as it should...
* CHG: Changed the icons for the track rating system - thanks Frank!
* CHG: Changed the icons for Postnuke and added a better discussion icon - thanks again to Frank!
* BUG: Changed the sort of the themes in the drop down box (if enabled) to alphabetical

