Jinzora 0.9.3 (12.9.03)

* SEC: Big Security Fix! Changed access level from Cookie to a session variable - Thanks very much Sean!!!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added the ability for Jinzora to automatically search for album art when viewing an artist (can be disabled, it is kinda slow...)
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a tool to list all missing album art to allow for MUCH faster searching for many covers
* NEW: Big Addition! Added #EXTM3U playlist format, playlists are MUCH prettier now (only supported by Winamp I think...)
* NEW: Big Addition! Made user authenication use Postnuke/PHPNuke user database! In PHP/Postnuke mode there is a new user manager!
* NEW: Big Addition! Also a standalone user manager!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added support for reading info (name, bitrate, etc) from the following file types:
  aac,ape,asf,au,avr,bonk,flac,id3v1,id3v2,la,lpac,lyrics3,matroska
  midi,mod,monkey,mp3,mpc,mpeg,nsv,ogg,ogginfo,optimfrog,quicktime
  real,rgad,riff,swf,voc,vqf
* NEW: Big Addition! Addition of a full help system. While it's not the end all - be all of help systems, it's much better than most!
* NEW: Big Addition! Now when viewing a folder, if it has no subfolder Jinzora assumes its an album and displays it as such!
* NEW: Big Addition! Added a new "file" caching system, you can now cache to local files to make everything MUCH faster - please see online docs for details
* NEW: Big Change! Added caching functionallity to Jinzora. Now all header information is read only once then reused, MUCH faster!
* NEW: Added a new "Random Album" image item to the Artist page. When in Genre/Artist/Album mode and viewing a specific Genre random album art from that Genre will show (if you want)
* NEW: Added the ability to put images on the Genre/Artist pages for each item. Just create an image with the EXACT same name of the folder, at the same level of the folder
* NEW: Added a new layout design on the Genre page (the page that lists the contents of a Genre) adding a picture and text at the top of the page
* NEW: Added the ability to NOT keep the porportions on images when Jinzora does the resizing. This is OFF by default
* NEW: Added the ability to hide the ID3 comment field when displaying tracks (if you don't want to see it)
* NEW: Added the ability to force the size of pictures on the tracks page WITHOUT actually resizing the images
* NEW: Updated the search results page for easier displaying...
* NEW: Added the ability to more easily embed Jinzora in an existing website (please see the documentation section for more details)
* NEW: Added a field next to Genres and/or Artists to show the number of sub items - off by default
* NEW: Added a "remember me" box at login. Basically write a 365 day cookie
* NEW: Added the ability to "Exclude" Genres/Artists from view, per user (by clicking the "More" icon)
* NEW: Added the ability to "Show Hidden" and remove the exclude list from above
* NEW: Added a "Power User" that can view, play, and download music
* NEW: Added the ability to download single tracks as MP3's instead as Zips (requested)
* NEW: Added a "Fake Track" display. If you create a file called "XXXXXXX.fake.txt" it will be displayed and it's contents will be the description (requested)
* NEW: Added a "Survey" link to the tools page, yeah, I know, but we just want to know more so we can make Jinzora better!!!
* NEW: Addition of Arabic language file (thanks Dooby)
* NEW: When searching it will give you the search term and number of matches in the header
* NEW: You can now specify a username:password to be prepended to URLs for playlist generation (for secured sites)
* NEW: Added a drop down box in the header for Tracks. Displays an alpha list of ALL tracks in Jinzora (can be PAINFULLY slow on big sites) (requested)
* NEW: Added a "Play Playlist" link on the playlist page. You can grab the URL and send a playlist to anyone (without them having any access to Jinzora)
* BUG: Fixed a issue when displaying files where the TAG information is blank (file name will be displayed, minus the extension and track number)
* BUG: Moving artists and renaming albums now works (thanks for all the help Will!)
* BUG: Fixed Jinzora through SSL. Now if in SSL it will stay in SSL and playlists will be SSL
* BUG: Fixed a bug where if there was more than one image in a album they would all be shown, now only the first one gets shown
* BUG: Made the "Tools" link show in PHPNuke mode - sorry guys...
* BUG: Fixed some issues with directory caching in 2 directory mode
* BUG: Fixed an issue with the lyrics file link and updated the display of this (now opens a popup window, am I evil?)
* BUG: Removed a few final areas that a view only user could use to play music - no music for you!
* BUG: Made lots of updates to the installer, hopefully this will help those of you with issues out!
* BUG: Fixed some issues with album art resizing leaving old file names around...
* BUG: Fixed a caching issue with Album art. Now when new art is downloaded it will display right the first time it's viewed
* BUG: Minor changes to the Postnuke/PHPNuke stylesheet
* BUG: Fixed an issue when trying to view " - New Playlist - " which obviously doesn't exist!
* CHG: Now when you click on an album cover it takes you to the album instead of playing it, you can click "Play Album" below to play it
* CHG: I cut down the sample track that is included from 4.5MB to 500k for smaller downloads
* CHG: Made the search functionality use the session cache information, MUCH faster!!!
* CHG: Removed the "Jinzora is not secure, please...." message in the footer, was just causing too many problems...
